response.Q0: I was initially testing to see if there was any correlation between distance from the centre to cash prize availability. Once I did that I then rotated between two or three end nodes as I thought I noticed a pattern where they paid out fairly regularly in proportion to negative payments they put out. Towards the end of the game I started employing this strategy without inspecting so I could maximise the money I would take.
response.Q1: I thought I was developing a strategy based on perceived patterns I thought I was noticing, but in the last few turns I wish I'd reverted to inspecting prior to moving as I don't think the risk-reward ratio was worth it.
response.Q2: I found it difficult as it was hard to judge whether the strategies I tested was based on real results or perceived patterns I noticed that weren't actually there. A trial and error approach, that I was using, was therefore difficult to measure based on the outcomes.

response.Q0: It took me some time to understand the game from reading the rules prior, I think a demonstration video would have been helpful as well. The practice games were useful.
